{{Infobox book | name = Garment of Shadows | title_orig = | translator = | image = Garment of Shadows.jpg | caption = | author = [[Laurie R. King]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = [[Mary Russell (fictional)|Mary Russell]] | subject = | genre = [[Detective fiction]] | publisher = [[File:Flag of the United States.svg|25px|United States]] [[Bantam Press]] | release_date = 2012 | media_type = Print (hardback) | pages = 266 | isbn = 978-0-7490-1222-9 | dewey = | congress = PS3561.I4813 G37 2012 | oclc = | preceded_by = [[Pirate King (Mary Russell novel)|Pirate King]] | followed_by = [[Dreaming Spies]] }}
'''''Garment of Shadows''''' is a 2012 mystery novel by American author [[Laurie R. King]]. Twelfth in the [[Mary Russell (fictional)|Mary Russell]] series, the story features married detectives Mary Russell and [[Sherlock Holmes]]. The events of the novel follow that of ''[[Pirate King (Mary Russell novel)|Pirate King]]'' and feature their old friends, Ali and Mahmoud Hazr (''[[O Jerusalem (novel)|O Jerusalem]]'' & ''[[Justice Hall]]'').
At the end of 1924, Mary Russell has just finished a stint with Fflytte Films in [[Morocco]] but she is not where she should be when her husband, Sherlock Holmes, goes to meet her in Fez. In fact, when she awakens in a strange room she does not know where or who she is, having taken a great blow to the head.
